{"TopicDetails": {"type": 0, "ccm2Id": 44544395, "cftId": 0, "identifier": "JUST-2022-JTRA", "title": "Call for proposals for action grants to support transnational projects on judicial training covering civil law, criminal law or fundamental rights", "publicationDateLong": 1637539200000, "callIdentifier": "JUST-2022-JTRA", "callTitle": "Call for proposals for action grants to support transnational projects on judicial training covering civil law, criminal law or fundamental rights", "callccm2Id": 44544401, "allowPartnerSearch": true, "workProgrammepart": {"id": 6094, "ccm_id": 44544743, "wp_part": "JUST-2022", "wp_year": "JUST-2022", "wp_title": "JUST-2022", "wp_website": "https://ec.europa.eu/info/departments/justice-and-consumers/justice-and-consumers-funding-tenders_en", "wp_document": "https://ec.europa.eu/info/departments/justice-and-consumers/justice-and-consumers-funding-tenders/funding-programmes_en"}, "frameworkProgramme": {"id": 43252386, "abbreviation": "JUST2027", "description": "Justice Programme (JUST)"}, "programmeDivision": [{"id": 43443701, "abbreviation": "JUST.1.2", "description": "Judicial training"}], "topicMGAs": [], "tags": ["criminal law", "judicial", "cross-border training", "fundamental rights", "radicalisation", "court interpreters", "judicial trainers", "training judiciary", "prosecutor", "violent extremism", "lawyer", "court translators", "mediators", "prison staff", "JUST-2022-JTRA", "rule of law", "probation staff", "court officer", "judicial ethics", "probation", "prison", "court coordinators", "bailiffs", "judicial staff", "insolvency practitioners", "judgecraft", "notaries", "civil law", "judge", "insolvency law", "legal practitioner"], "sme": false, "actions": [{"status": {"id": 31094503, "abbreviation": "Closed", "description": "Closed"}, "types": [{"typeOfAction": "JUST-PJG JUST Project Grants", "typeOfMGA": [{"id": 43250237, "abbreviation": "JUST-AG", "description": "JUST Action Grant Budget-Based"}]}], "plannedOpeningDate": "15 December 2021", "submissionProcedure": {"id": 31094504, "abbreviation": "single-stage", "description": "single-stage"}, "deadlineDates": ["22 March 2022"]}], "latestInfos": [{"approvalDate": "Jul 8, 2022 4:58:12 PM", "lastChangeDate": "Jul 8, 2022 4:58:12 PM", "content": "<p>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://file:///U:/9.%20JUSTICE/by2021-2022/2.%20AG/2022/JTRA/2.%20Evaluation/Call%20Update%20Flash%20Info%20JTRA%202022.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Call update flash info &ndash; call results</a></p>"}], "budgetOverviewJSONItem": {"budgetTopicActionMap": {"3410807": [{"action": "JUST-2022-JTRA - JUST-PJG JUST Project Grants", "plannedOpeningDate": "15 December 2021", "deadlineModel": "single-stage", "deadlineDates": ["22 March 2022"], "budgetYearMap": {"2022": 5000000}, "budgetTopicActionMap": {}}]}, "budgetYearsColumns": ["2022"]}, "description": "<SPAN class=\"topicdescriptionkind\">Scope</SPAN>:<p><span>The objective of the call is to contribute to the effective and coherent application of EU law in the areas of civil law, criminal law and fundamental rights, as enshrined in the EU Charter of Fundamental Rights, and the rule of law related issues, by helping to address the training needs of justice professionals in these fields. </span></p><p>The priorities of 2022 will concentrate funding on training activities and tools for training providers, as described below, in order to support cross-border training activities:</p><ol level=\"0\">  <li>for justice professionals, and/or</li><li>for multipliers, such as judicial trainers or EU law court coordinators, where there are guarantees that the multipliers will pass on their knowledge to justice professionals in a systematic way, and/or</li><li>for cross-professional training, in order to stimulate discussions across judicial professions about the application of EU law and contribute to a European judicial culture across professional boundaries on precisely identified topics of relevance to the concerned professions.</li> </ol><p>For more information please see the <a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/docs/2021-2027/just/wp-call/2021-2022/call-fiche_just-2022-jtra_en.pdf\"><span style=\"color:#0000FF;\"><strong>Call document</strong></span></a>.</p>\n", "conditions": "<p><b style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:&#10;normal\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&#10;&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\">1.<span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:&#10;bold\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Eligible countries</span></b><span style=\"font-size:&#10;9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;&#10;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\">:&nbsp;as described in the <a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/docs/2021-2027/just/wp-call/2021-2022/call-fiche_just-2022-jtra_en.pdf \" target=\"_blank\">Call document</a>.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;&#10;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;&#10;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\">Member States of the European Union (including their overseas departments), excluding Denmark.</span><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;&#10;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;&#10;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\n<p><b><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;&#10;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;&#10;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\">2.&nbsp;&nbsp; Eligibility and admissibility conditions:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;&#10;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\"> as described in the </span><span style=\"font-size:&#10;9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;&#10;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\"><a href=\"ht